      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that it's about different values, but surely there's more to it than just opinion? like, when you look at the actual outcomes in countries that have it versus the US, doesn't that make the \"human right\" side more of a reality than just a theory? it feels like the \"inefficient takeover\" argument is mostly just used to protect insurance companies.",
