      "content": "okay but if the stats show that universal coverage works better for people's health and costs less overall, wouldn't calling it an \"inefficient takeover\" just be factually wrong? like, if the data proves it's more effective, at what point does it stop being a \"debate\" and just become a proven better way to run things?",
